3.2 Configuring Authentication
==============================

You need to add your Instapaper credentials to an ‘auth-source’ file.
There are two main options:

* Menu:

* Plain Text Credentials::      Using ~/.authinfo
* Encrypted Credentials::       Using ~/.authinfo.gpg (recommended)


File: read-later.info,  Node: Plain Text Credentials,  Next: Encrypted Credentials,  Up: Configuring Authentication

3.2.1 Plain Text Credentials
----------------------------

Create or edit ‘~/.authinfo’ and add:

     machine www.instapaper.com login your-email@example.com password your-password

   *Important:* This file stores credentials in plain text.  Secure it
with:

     chmod 600 ~/.authinfo


File: read-later.info,  Node: Encrypted Credentials,  Prev: Plain Text Credentials,  Up: Configuring Authentication

3.2.2 Encrypted Credentials (Recommended)
-----------------------------------------

For better security, use an encrypted file:

  1. Create or edit ‘~/.authinfo.gpg’

  2. Add the same line as the plain text version:

          machine www.instapaper.com login your-email@example.com password your-password

  3. Save the file (Emacs will prompt you to encrypt it with GPG)

   Ensure GPG is configured in Emacs:

     (require 'epa-file)
     (epa-file-enable)


