6.1 Authentication Issues
=========================

If you see "‘✗ Authentication failed’":

  1. Verify your credentials in ‘~/.authinfo’ or ‘~/.authinfo.gpg’

  2. Ensure you're using your actual Instapaper email and password

  3. Run ‘M-x read-later-test-auth’ to test authentication

  4. Check that the machine name is exactly ‘www.instapaper.com’

  5. Verify the format is: ‘machine www.instapaper.com login EMAIL
     password PASSWORD’


File: read-later.info,  Node: Credential Issues,  Next: GPG Issues,  Prev: Authentication Issues,  Up: Troubleshooting

6.2 Credential Issues
=====================

If auth-source can't find your credentials, ensure it's configured
correctly:

     (setq auth-sources '("~/.authinfo.gpg" "~/.authinfo"))

   Check which files auth-source is searching:

     (message "auth-sources: %s" auth-sources)


File: read-later.info,  Node: GPG Issues,  Next: Network Issues,  Prev: Credential Issues,  Up: Troubleshooting

6.3 GPG Issues
==============

If you have trouble with ‘.authinfo.gpg’:

  1. Ensure GPG is installed:

          gpg --version

  2. Configure EPA (EasyPG) in Emacs:

          (require 'epa-file)
          (epa-file-enable)

  3. Test decryption by opening ‘~/.authinfo.gpg’ in Emacs


File: read-later.info,  Node: Network Issues,  Prev: GPG Issues,  Up: Troubleshooting

6.4 Network Issues
==================

If you experience network problems:

  1. Check your internet connection

  2. Enable debug logging:

          (setq url-debug t)

  3. Check the ‘*URL-DEBUG*’ buffer for detailed error messages

  4. Verify you can reach Instapaper:

          curl -I https://www.instapaper.com/api/authenticate


