7.1 Interactive Functions
=========================

 -- Command: read-later

     Open the Instapaper bookmarks buffer.  Displays a tabulated list of
     your bookmarks with titles, reading progress, tags, and
     descriptions.

     In the bookmarks buffer:
        • Press ‘RET’ to open a bookmark in your browser
        • Press ‘g’ to refresh the bookmark list

     This is an interactive command that can be invoked with ‘M-x’.

     *Example:*
          M-x read-later

 -- Command: read-later-update

     Refresh the bookmarks buffer with the latest data from Instapaper.
     This command updates the bookmark list to show any changes made on
     other devices or through the Instapaper website.

     This is an interactive command that can be invoked with ‘M-x’ or by
     pressing ‘g’ in the bookmarks buffer.

     *Example:*
          M-x read-later-update

 -- Command: read-later-add-url-at-point

     Add the URL at point to Instapaper.  Detects the URL under the
     cursor using ‘thing-at-point’ and sends it to your Instapaper
     account.

     This is an interactive command that can be invoked with ‘M-x’.

     *Example:*
          M-x read-later-add-url-at-point

 -- Command: read-later-interactively-add-url url

     Prompt for a URL and add it to Instapaper.  You'll be asked to
     enter the URL in the minibuffer.

     This is an interactive command that can be invoked with ‘M-x’.

     *Arguments:*
     URL
          The URL to add to Instapaper (prompted interactively).

     *Example:*
          M-x read-later-interactively-add-url RET
          https://example.com/article RET

 -- Command: read-later-add-elfeed-entry-at-point

     Add the elfeed entry at point to Instapaper.  This command should
     be used in the elfeed search buffer.  It extracts the URL from the
     selected feed entry and sends it to Instapaper.

     Requires the ‘elfeed’ package to be installed.

     This is an interactive command that can be invoked with ‘M-x’.

     *Example:*
          ;; In elfeed-search-mode buffer
          M-x read-later-add-elfeed-entry-at-point

 -- Command: read-later-test-auth

     Test authentication with Instapaper.  Sends a request to the
     Instapaper authentication endpoint and displays whether
     authentication succeeded.

     This is useful for verifying your credentials are configured
     correctly.

     This is an interactive command that can be invoked with ‘M-x’.

     *Returns:* Displays a message indicating success or failure.

     *Example:*
          M-x read-later-test-auth
          ;; => "✓ Authentication successful!"


